{
  "query": "What actions can be taken to mitigate the environmental pollution caused by waste from salmon farms?",
  "answer": "Integrated aquaculture systems and waste management strategies can help mitigate pollution from salmon farms, with some methods showing promising results in waste absorption and water quality improvement.\n\nSeveral approaches can be implemented to address salmon farm pollution. Integrated aquaculture systems have shown potential, with studies demonstrating that blue mussels can effectively absorb waste from salmon farms [932]. This same approach has also benefited other species, with scallops showing increased growth when placed next to fish farms, and enhanced algal growth observed adjacent to fish farming operations [932]. Water treatment before release into the environment has shown positive effects, with one study demonstrating improved conditions for characteristic plant species and decreased vascular plant biomass in affected areas [1778]. Several preventive measures have been identified, including minimizing food waste in aquaculture systems [2744] and improving fish food and pellets to reduce waste production at the source [2192], though these approaches still require further study to confirm their effectiveness. It's worth noting that while some methods show promise, not all integrated systems may be effective, as evidenced by one study that found no indication of oysters and mussels feeding on fish farm waste [932].",
  "action_ids": [
    "932",
    "1778",
    "2744",
    "2192"
  ]
}

